"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-cyril-ramaphosa-to-celebrate-south-africa-2024-paris-olympics-paralympics-medallists\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.998880872074854, \"rank\": 0.001120042021184128, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbCyril Ramaphosa to belatedly celebrate SA's 2024 Paris Olympics, Paralympics medallists  Athletes who represented South Africa at the 2024 Paris Olympic and Paralympic Games will be celebrated at an event on Friday.\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.998880872074854, \"rank\": 0.001120042021184128, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 184, \"end\": 199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyril_Ramaphosa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cyril Ramaphosa\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyril_Ramaphosa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyril_Ramaphosa\"}, {\"begin\": 223, \"end\": 225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9368041528574155e-35, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 298, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.24108794952311e-20, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.7556634598134053, \"rank\": 0.195388093453103, \"text\": \"Paralympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes who representedSouth Africaat the 2024 Paris Olympic and Paralympic Gameswill be celebratedat an event hosted by PresidentCyril Ramaphosaon Friday, 29 November at a ceremony at the Union Buildings.\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED |Gayton McKenzie's trip to 2024 Paris Olympics cost SA taxpayers R800 000  \\\"The ceremony will recognise the excellence demonstrated by top athletes as well as the organisational effort by the South African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee to prepare Team South Africa for the Games.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gayton_McKenzie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gayton McKenzie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gayton_McKenzie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gayton_McKenzie\"}, {\"begin\": 669, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9368041528574155e-35, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Team South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Team South Africa featured 147 athletes at the Paris Olympics Games, which took place from 26 July to 11 August 2024, and 32 athletes at the Paris Summer Paralympics Games from 28 August to 8 September 2024,\\\" said the Presidency.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of12medals were achieved for the respective games.\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sixeach for the Olympics - one gold, three silver and two bronze - and Paralympics -two gold and four bronze.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The appreciation ceremony will include the conferring of awards to deserving athletes and their coaches as well as the Shield of Jove, which is the highest South African recognition in sports achievement following the Olympic and Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's still unclear whether South Africa's Olympic and Paralympic athletes have been paid.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.24108794952311e-20, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To the best of The South African website's knowledge, there has been no handing over of cheques to those who walked away with gold, silver or bronze medals in Paris.\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.562841626624814e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture,Gayton McKenzie, had said that a 'big surprise' awaits South Africa's medal winners at the\\u00a0Paris Olympics 2024.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1912, \"end\": 1924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.24108794952311e-20, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It remains unclear what that 'big surprise' was.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a reminder, these were the promised incentives for medal winners:  IndividualsGold medallists R400 000, coach R100 000Silver medallists R200 000, coach R50 000Bronze medallists R75 000, coach R25 000  Relays and team sportsGold medal: R100 000 per player/athlete, coach R100 000Silver medal: R75 000 per player/athlete, coach R75 000Bronze medal: R50 000 per player/athlete, coach R50 000  Boats (2 athletes)Gold medal: R200 000, coach R100 000Silver medal: R100 000, coach R50 000Bronze medal: R40 000, coach R20\\u00a0000  GOLD (1)- Tatjana Smith (women's 100m breaststroke)  SILVERS (3)- Tatjana Smith (women's 200m breaststroke), men's 4x100m relay team, Jo-Ane van Dyk (women's javelin)  BRONZES (2)- Alan Hatherly (men's mountain bike cross country), rugby sevens team  GOLD (2)- Mpumelelo Mhlongo (men's 100m - T44), Simone Kruger (women's Discus Throw - F38)  SILVERS (0)-  BRONZES (4)- Mpumelelo Mhlongo (men's 200m - T64), Louzanne Coetzee (women's 1 500m - T11), Pieter du Preez (men's H1 Individual Time Trial), Donald Ramphadi and Lucas Sihole (men's tennis quad doubles)  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or by emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.comor sending a WhatsApp to060 011 021 1  Subscribeto The South African website's newsletters and follow us on@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor the latest news.\", \"from\": 2020, \"to\": 3377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renault_R40\", \"score\": 0.999982853426566, \"rank\": 1.256437800645933e-05, \"text\": \"R40\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renault_R40\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renault_R40\"}, {\"begin\": 2676, \"end\": 2690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jo-Ane van Dyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\"}, {\"begin\": 2723, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"score\": 0.9999924602050241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alan Hatherly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\"}, {\"begin\": 2864, \"end\": 2876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discus_throw\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Discus Throw\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discus_throw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discus_throw\"}, {\"begin\": 2879, \"end\": 2882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9797520097646507e-56, \"text\": \"F38\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para-athl